CreateLaunchTemplate.description: This example creates a Spot fleet request with two launch specifications that differ only by subnet. If the instances are launched in a nondefault VPC, they do not receive a public IP address by default. Note that you can't specify different subnets from the same Availability Zone in a Spot fleet request.

If your account supports EC2-VPC only, Amazon EC2 launches the Spot instances in the default subnet of the Availability Zone. If your account supports EC2-Classic, Amazon EC2 launches the instances in EC2-Classic in the Availability Zone.
